    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SHIFT KNOB (ROADRANGER VALVE)</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303215">Figure 15.</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303215" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303215.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Shift Knob (Roadranger Valve)</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>A sudden release of air pressure can cause personal injury or damage to equipment. To prevent
                        injury or equipment damage, exhaust the vehicle air tanks.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The air lines must be depressurized.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two (2) mounting screws from the shift knob cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the cover down to access the air fittings.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the air lines from the air fittings.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the jam nut from the valve base.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unscrew the valve and remove it from the shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
